FYI: Corruption errors are very common when you're trying to install MS developer tools off of daemon tools or whatever. Just extract the whole ISO to a folder and run install from there, then it works great.

2005 doesn't handle Vista well. For everything, right click and "Install as Administrator" Get SP1 and then Vista compatability patch.

It will still give a warning, but just alter your shortcut properties to always run as admin, and then click the ignore warning checkbox when it comes up
